      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "INTEMPERANCE (7) made an impressive start to his career when he beat race rival GOCCIADORO to score by more than 8m at this circuit and distance. Draws much wider but looks a talent and has plenty of upside. DISTURBANCE (8) has looked good in cruising home by more than 15m in his two starts to date, drawing on the back row and racing three wide in the latter stages before drawing right away last time at Bathurst. Draws out but has the speed to push forward. GOCCIADORO (6) led as favourite and was unable to see it out behind INTEMPERANCE last start but that was his first run for six weeks so it should have improved him. Yet to miss the top-two, finishing 4.6m away in the Gold Crown Final two back so he is worth another chance. PASSION AND PAIN (10) continued his good form when he came from this row to win last start at Penrith. Include.",
